-- ECB discussed bond buys of 1 trillion euros or more - German paper 
-- By Paul Carrel and John O'Donnell
-- Fri Dec 05, 2014 08:28AM EST
-- None



FRANKFURT, Dec 5 (Reuters) - The European Central Bank discussed a bond purchase programme with a volume of more than 1 trillion euros ($1.24 trillion) at its meetings this week, the German newspaper Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeiting (FAZ) reported on Friday.

"It concerned an extension of the balance sheet by more than the 1 trillion euros that has been talked about in public," the FAZ reported, citing an insider from the Eurosystem of euro zone central banks. The ECB Governing Council met on Wednesday and Thursday.